nbsEusmTestGrp.name: nbsEusmTestGrp
nbsEusmTestGrp.description: Testing category of features for EUSM boards. The example items that may go here are the smart loopback traffic generation, loss/gain analysis, performance monitoring, etc.

nbsEusmSlotTable.name: nbsEusmSlotTable
nbsEusmSlotTable.description: Contains a description of slot context features applicable for the whole module. There is going to be one row for each slot. All the scalar type objects applicable at the slot context are dumped here.

nbsEusmSlotEntry.name: nbsEusmSlotEntry
nbsEusmSlotEntry.description: Contains a description of slot context features applicable for the whole module. There is going to be one row for each slot. All the scalar type objects applicable at the slot context are dumped here.

nbsEusmSlotSupportsEusm.name: nbsEusmSlotSupportsEusm
nbsEusmSlotSupportsEusm.description: Is EUSM config and status supported for this slot?

nbsEusmSlotAccControlActionUntag.name: nbsEusmSlotAccControlActionUntag
nbsEusmSlotAccControlActionUntag.description: permit(2) or deny(3) works on all untagged frames

nbsEusmSlotAccControlActionTag.name: nbsEusmSlotAccControlActionTag
nbsEusmSlotAccControlActionTag.description: denyAll(2) filters all tagged frames denyVlan(3) and permitVlan(4) work on the specified list permitAll(5) negates access control of tagged frames

nbsEusmSlotAccControlVidList.name: nbsEusmSlotAccControlVidList
nbsEusmSlotAccControlVidList.description: List of VLAN in a free format, for example 10-12 15 23-43 1000-1050 specifies 3 different ranges of vlan ids and one isolated vlan id

nbsEusmSlotLinkAggrAdmin.name: nbsEusmSlotLinkAggrAdmin
nbsEusmSlotLinkAggrAdmin.description: Depending on the link status of the trunk ports the Link Aggregation operational status may be different, this is why it calls for both Admin and Oper objects

nbsEusmSlotStormControlBroadcast.name: nbsEusmSlotStormControlBroadcast
nbsEusmSlotStormControlBroadcast.description: User-specified maximum allowed Broadcast frames, in units of 1000 frames/second. The value zero (0) indicates this feature is disabled, so no cap will be enforced.

nbsEusmSlotStormControlMulticast.name: nbsEusmSlotStormControlMulticast
nbsEusmSlotStormControlMulticast.description: User-specified maximum allowed Multicast frames, in units of 1000 frames/second. The value zero (0) indicates this feature is disabled, so no cap will be enforced.

nbsEusmSlotStormControlUnicast.name: nbsEusmSlotStormControlUnicast
nbsEusmSlotStormControlUnicast.description: User-specified maximum allowed Unicast frames, in units of 1000 frames/second. The value zero (0) indicates this feature is disabled, so no cap will be enforced.

nbsEusmSlotCoSMode.name: nbsEusmSlotCoSMode
nbsEusmSlotCoSMode.description: If the user selects bothTagDscp(4), and a packet arrives with both DSCP and a Vlan tag, the DSCP priority system will take precedence. tagOnly(3) will use Layer 2 Vlan Priority bits to assign a Service Level Class (SLC) to a packet and tagMappingTable information will be used. dscpOnly(2) will use Layer 3 DSCP bits to assign an SL class to a packet. dscpMappingTable information will be used

nbsEusmSlotDscpRemark.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpRemark
nbsEusmSlotDscpRemark.description: The EUSM can be set to mark egress packets with a new DSCP. The user can set to remark egress DSCP in one of the following modes: AF or CS Remarking only applies to IPv4 or IPv6 packets. The user can define which type of incoming (ingress )DSCP frames will be remarked.Selection includes the combination of EF,AF,CS,Zero DSCP and all others.

nbsEusmSlotDscpEgressMode.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpEgressMode
nbsEusmSlotDscpEgressMode.description: The user can set to egress remark DSCP in one of the following modes: a) Map CoS class to AF CPs (call it AF-mode) 0: AF12 1: AF22 2: AF32 3: AF42 b) Map CoS class to Class selectors CPs (call it CS-mode) 0: 000000 1: 001000 2: 010000 3: 110000

nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressEf.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressEf
nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressEf.description: One of the five ingress options EF,AF,CS,ZERO and OTHER

nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressAf.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressAf
nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressAf.description: One of the five ingress options EF,AF,CS,ZERO and OTHER

nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressCs.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressCs
nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressCs.description: One of the five ingress options EF,AF,CS,ZERO and OTHER

nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressZeroDscp.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressZeroDscp
nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressZeroDscp.description: One of the five ingress options EF,AF,CS,ZERO and OTHER

nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressAllOther.name: nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressAllOther
nbsEusmSlotDscpIngressAllOther.description: One of the five ingress options EF,AF,CS,ZERO and OTHER

nbsEusmSlotIometrix.name: nbsEusmSlotIometrix
nbsEusmSlotIometrix.description: Controls whether or not the EUSM should enable Iometrix Level 1 cNode agent behavior

nbsEusmSlotManagementVid.name: nbsEusmSlotManagementVid
nbsEusmSlotManagementVid.description: VLAN Id reserved for EUSM management activities.

nbsEusmSlotUserPortIRAdmin.name: nbsEusmSlotUserPortIRAdmin
nbsEusmSlotUserPortIRAdmin.description: Unit is kilobits per second. Max possible value is 4,294,967,295 which is large enough even to represent 1 Terabit communication. This applies to user ingress traffic that does not match any defined flow. 0 is acceptable value, which means discard all non-flow traffic. Any value above 1000000 for EUSM is considered as no limit.

nbsEusmSlotUserPortIROper.name: nbsEusmSlotUserPortIROper
nbsEusmSlotUserPortIROper.description: Unit is kilobits per second. Max possible value is 4,294,967,295 which is large enough even to represent 1 Terabit communication. This is the actual value applied to user ingress traffic that does not match any defined flow. It is based on the configured IRAdmin object modified to match the constraints of the device.

nbsEusmSlotMaxVlanTranSize.name: nbsEusmSlotMaxVlanTranSize

nbsEusmSlotMaxDscpMapSize.name: nbsEusmSlotMaxDscpMapSize
nbsEusmSlotMaxDscpMapSize.description: Maximum number of entries in the DSCP to SLC Priority Map table. This may vary from slot to slot if different versions of EUSM software support different table sizes.

nbsEusmSlotMaxCosPrioSize.name: nbsEusmSlotMaxCosPrioSize
nbsEusmSlotMaxCosPrioSize.description: Maximum number of entries in the VLAN CoS to SLC Priority table. This may vary from slot to slot if different versions of EUSM software support different table sizes.

nbsEusmTgaInterPacketGap.name: nbsEusmTgaInterPacketGap
nbsEusmTgaInterPacketGap.description: Rate Control - only option is fixed. Default is 1249928. This sets an approx rate of 100/10/1 fps at 1000/100/10 Mbps. Number of bytes between frames. Controls traffic rate

nbsEusmTgaAction.name: nbsEusmTgaAction
nbsEusmTgaAction.description: Different actions to activate the traffic generation. There are three frame generation activities: specify, start, and stop. Specifying and actually starting traffic may be done together or separately. In fact, it is reasonable to specify once, then start (and stop) many times.

nbsEusmCableTestStatus.name: nbsEusmCableTestStatus
nbsEusmCableTestStatus.description: To initiate and get the status of the cable test feature. It is applicable only to copper ports. In the future we may have multiple copper ports. A GET on this object will show testIdle if a test has never been run, or testCompleted(4) if it has. When testStart(2) is SET, for a short time of about 3 seconds you would expect to see testInProgress(3). Time-stamp of the test start will be sent by the SNMP agent to the line-card to keep track of the time instance of the test.

nbsEusmCableTestResult.name: nbsEusmCableTestResult
nbsEusmCableTestResult.description: This string will give out the result of the cable test done with a time stamp that gives the indication as to when the CableTest was initiated. This also gives the result for all the 4 pairs of wire. Possible results status includes invalid, good, mismatch short and open. When the status is mismatch, short or open, there will be length indicating more information about the location of the fault. From the LNXNM point of view it is easy to deal with scalars than tables - so this is made into DisplayString. Since the MVs use it read-only and display anyway, it is probably simpler to deal with scalar display string rather than table. An example TestResult may look like the following <time-stamp>pair-1 good,pair-2 invalid,pair-3 open at 25 meters,pair-4 good.

nbsEusmSlotPmInterval.name: nbsEusmSlotPmInterval
nbsEusmSlotPmInterval.description: Performance Monitoring time duration (sec). Practical range allowed is 1 minute to 1 week.

nbsEusmSlotPmSelector.name: nbsEusmSlotPmSelector
nbsEusmSlotPmSelector.description: Performance Monitoring traffic direction selector. coToCpe(2) measures from CO's active trunk port to CPE's active trunk port. cpeToCo(3) measures from CPE's active trunk port to CO's active trunk port. To measure from one CPE to another, the user should designate the source CPE as cpeTx(4) and the destination CPE as cpeRx(5). The reflector CPE must be activated before the source CPE.

nbsEusmSlotPmCapabilities.name: nbsEusmSlotPmCapabilities
nbsEusmSlotPmCapabilities.description: This bitmask indicates which performance monitoring selectors this slot can support. This object is mandatory for all slots in systems where the nbsEusmSlotPmSelector object is supported. Each capability is represented by one bit. Set bit to 1 to advertise capability, 0 to deny it. Capability Bit -------------- --- reserved 0 notSupported 1 coToCpe 2 cpeToCo 3 cpeTx 4 cpeRx 5 OCTET STRING bitmasks count the leftmost bit (MSB) as 0. A zero length OCTET STRING indicates that this object is not supported.
